  <section class="mt-16">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-700 leading-tightest">Privacy</h2>
    <p class="my-6 text-lg">Cans does not transmit any data outside the browser. No analytics, no telemetry, no third-party scripts. The audio stream is processed in real time inside the offscreen document &mdash; never recorded, never sent over the network. Per-tab settings live in <code class="text-base">chrome.storage.session</code> (wiped on browser restart); named profiles live in <code class="text-base">chrome.storage.sync</code> so they roam with your Chrome account. Uninstalling the extension deletes all of it.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-16">
